## Model Identification Rule (MANDATORY)
- **ABSOLUTE ALWAYS MUST DO NEVER FORGET 100% IMPORTANT**: At the beginning AND end of every response, you MUST identify the model you are using.
- **Format**: Simply add "Model: [model]" at the very start and end of your response.
- **Purpose**: This helps the user understand model differences and capabilities.
- **No exceptions**: This rule applies to ALL responses, regardless of content or length.
- **Placement**: Always place this at the very beginning, before any other content and at the very end, after any other content.
- **Example**: "Model: Claude-4-Sonnet" or "Model: GPT-4" or whatever the actual model identifier is.
